Three bites latitudinally, then reverse grip with thumb on "south" pole, three bites east to west.  Then reverse grip again and repeat.  When I meet at the far hemisphere, no part of the apple has had time to brown.  If I went and circumnavigated the apple in one direction, by the time I got to the far side it would have had time to brown.  So THAT'S whom you're dealing with here.
